Saudi signs $ 117 mln water distribution contract . Saudi Arabia has signed a 441 million riyal ( $ 117 . 6 million ) contract to build a pumping station and two pipelines to distribute desalinated water in the kingdom ' s eastern province , newspapers reported on Monday . They said Agriculture and Water Minister Abdullah bin Abdul - Aziz bin Muammar signed the contract on Sunday with a Turkish company . They did not name the company and Turkish embassy officials were not available for comment . The newspapers said the project , which includes the construction of two pipelines carrying a total of 408 , 991 cubic metres of water a day , will be completed in two years . 
